The Houston Livestock Show and Rodeo is one of the largest events of its kind in the world, drawing over two million attendees annually to NRG Park. 
It combines a professional rodeo, live concerts, and a major livestock exhibition, all while raising millions for Texas scholarships and education.

As a media production intern I operated live broadcast cameras during livestock and horse show events at NRG Center and NRG Arena, while also providing audio assistance for staff and contracted professional crews. 
I stepped into broadcast control room roles including Director and Associate Director, and supported the team with ongoing news monitoring and collecting broadcast clips relevant to HLSR coverage.
